"I have a dark soul, that doesn't mean I don't love the sun, rainbows and things that emphasize the light.\n\n- Melody  Lee, Moon Gypsy\n|\nMan is not born to solve the problem of the universe, but to find out what he has to do; and to restrain himself within the limits of his comprehension.\n\n- Johann\n|\nI watched the spinning stars, grateful, sad and proud, as only a man who has outlived his destiny and realizes he might yet forge himself another, can be.\n\n- Roger Zelazny, Isle of the Dead\n|\nDo I love you? My God, if your love were a grain of sand, mine would be a universe of beaches.\n\n- William Goldman, The Princess Bride\n|\nArt and disease proliferate via contagion, and similar conditions favor both.\n\n- Ted Gioia, How to Listen to Jazz\n|\nThe Kingdom of God is about peace, love, joy and righteousness\n\n- Sunday\n|\nFocus on your goals, not your fear. Focus like a laser beam on your goals.\n\n- Roy T. Bennett, The Light in the Heart\n|\nNobody should be alone,' Sissix said. 'Being alone and untouched...there's no punishment worse than that. And she's done nothing wrong. She's just different.\n\n- Becky\n|\nThe luxury of being half-asleep, exploring the fringes of psychosis in safety.\n\n- Ian McEwan, Saturday\n|\nI think fish is nice, but then I think that rain is wet, so who am I to judge?\n\n- Douglas\n|\nEveryone is longing for love, everyone is suffering from the needs and wants, so be loving, kind, and compassionate to everyone.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nPray for faith, hope for peace, strive for unity, and persevere for harmony.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nNo matter how deep you bury good seeds, they always find a way to rise.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nLooking up at the stars only proves you admire them, but shining your light proves you are like them.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nThere in the sweet sacking smell of the mail bags he understood that he was dying, and it pleased him that he was going in the company of so many soft words home.\n\n- Chris Cleave, Everyone Brave is Forgiven\n|\nLast night I dreamt that somebody loved me.No hope, no harm; just another false alarm\n\n- Morrissey\n|\nI know. I was there. I saw the great void in your soul, and you saw mine.\n\n- Sebastian Faulks, Birdsong\n|\nIf people notice you only when you do something very strange, then you are very lucky! You can enjoy your life without being noticed as long as you don’t do anything very strange!\n\n- Mehmet\n|\nAlways be there for others. Always inspire them with your dreams and hope, vision and mission, attitude and aptitude.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nJosh: So, Toby, it’s election night. What do you say about a country that goes out of its way to protect even those citizens that try to destroy it?Toby: God bless America.\n\n- Aaron\n|\nSimply by changing our thoughts, we can sow the seeds of happiness in the garden of our minds.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nWe shouldn't have been so scornful; we should have had compassion. But compassion takes work, and we were young.\n\n- Margaret Atwood, The Year of the Flood\n|\nIf you find yourself engaged in an argument that only stirs anger in the heart, quickly make peace and carry on.\n\n- Suzy Kassem, Rise Up and Salute the Sun: The Writings of Suzy Kassem\n|\nHe mistook, as the cleverest men often do mistake, in underrating the cruelty of women.\n\n- Ouida, Wanda, Countess von Szalras.\n|\nWhen I am looking for you, then in silence, your every atom is longing for me.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nPeace is not only the absence of war, but the presence of harmony.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nIf life throws you a few bad notes or vibrations, don't let them interrupt or alter your song.\n\n- Suzy Kassem, Rise Up and Salute the Sun: The Writings of Suzy Kassem\n|\nWalking there, she said: Look, it seems like some one has kept each stone with measured precision at its place. Yes, she was right.\n\n- Mahrukh\n|\nIn her crazy, upside down world, she needed someone like that. A rock that would keep her going, an anchor to keep her from drifting away. Instead, she was alone\n\n- Kayla Krantz, Survive at Midnight\n|\nStart your day by awakening early to welcome the morning sun with a smile, love, and gratitude.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nWant coffee?' I asked, as I headed that way.'It's three thirty in the morning.''Okay. Want coffee?\n\n- Darynda Jones, Third Grave Dead Ahead\n|\nIf you are driven by fear, anger or pride nature will force you to compete. If you are guided by courage, awareness, tranquility and peace nature will serve you.\n\n- Amit Ray, Nonviolence: The Transforming Power\n|\nLes naturels sanguinaires à l'endroit des bestes, tesmoignent une propension naturelle à la cruauté.\n\n- Michel de Montaigne, The Complete Essays\n|\nYet tell me, my brothers: if a goal for humanity is still lacking, is there not still lacking--humanity itself?\n\n- Friedrich Nietzsche, A Nietzsche Reader\n|\nI wasn’t crying, but my heart was crying. I wasn’t feeling, but my heart was bleeding. Now I am crying, but my heart is healing. I am learning that I know nothing.\n\n- Benyf, 11.11.11 After so Many Years of Tears: Letters to My Distant Soul-Mate\n|\nAnd who did she have? The thought caught her up short, but then she smiled, remembering the preacher's words. She had the Lord. He was her foundation, and that was enough.\n\n- Carol Cox, Trouble in Store\n|\nIn everyday life, a blessed act of saying ‘hello, a smile, word of encouragement…’ can uplift someone spirit.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nThe nature of things is, I admit, a sturdy adversary.\n\n- Edmund Burke, The Letters on a Regicide Peace\n|\nI thought about how all that mattered, in all entirety, and all I wanted, and all I could see anything being worth anything for, was being a writer.\n\n- Ariel Schrag, Likewise: The High School Comic Chronicles of Ariel Schrag\n|\nTo wake the soul by tender strokes of art,To raise the genius, and to mend the heart\n\n- Alexander\n|\nThe bright flower was like a face. Somehow, the beauty and life of it were surprising in the 